The '''Micrococcineae''' are a suborder of [[bacteria]] of the order [[Actinomycetales]]. They are [[Gram-positive]] [[soil]] organisms, and are also [[paraphyletic]] with respect to the suborder [[Actinomycetineae]] and order [[Bifidobacteriales]], i.e. the [[Actinomycetineae]] and [[Bifidobacteriales]] are both nested within the clade Micrococcineae.

==Phylogeny==
The currently accepted phylogeny is based on 16S rRNA-based LTP release 123 by [[The All-Species Living Tree Project]] <ref>[[All-Species Living Tree Project]].{{cite web | url=http://www.arb-silva.de/fileadmin/silva_databases/living_tree/LTP_release_123/LTPs123_SSU_tree.pdf | title=16S rRNA-based LTP release 123 (full tree) | publisher=[[Silva Comprehensive Ribosomal RNA Database]] | accessdate=2016-11-17}}</ref>

