A '''prehomosexual''' is a person, usually a child, who may be a [[homosexual]] but is either undecided or predetermined.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=http://blogs.scientificamerican.com/bering-in-mind/is-your-child-a-prehomosexual-forecasting-adult-sexual-orientation/|title=Is your child a "prehomosexual"? Forecasting adult sexual orientation|work=Scientific American Blog Network|author=[[Jesse Bering]]|date=September 15, 2010|accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://jezebel.com/5641129/what-exactly-does-a-prehomosexual-look-like|title=What, Exactly, Does a "Prehomosexual" Look Like?|author=Gwen Sharpe|date=Sep 17, 2010|work=[[Jezebel (website)|Jezebel]]|accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref> A study by J. Michael Bailey and Kenneth Zucker suggests that  prehomosexuality may be recognized from "inverted pattern[s] of sex-typed childhood behaviors", such as boys interested in makeup or girls interested in sports. However this correlation is not perfect.<ref name=":0" />

