'''Stanley K. Abe''' is an [[art historian]] with [[Duke University]] and a specialist in [[Chinese art]] and [[Buddhist art]]. He received his BA, MA, and PhD from the [[University of California at Berkeley]].<ref>[https://aahvs.duke.edu/people/profile/stanley-abe Stanley Abe.] Duke University. Retrieved 13 June 2017.</ref> His book ''Ordinary images'' (2002) won the Freer Gallery/Smithsonian Institution: Shimada Prize.<ref>[http://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/O/bo3614235.html ''Ordinary Images'', Stanley K. Abe.] University of Chicago Press Books. Retrieved 13 June 2017.</ref>

