'''System appreciation''' is an activity often included in the maintenance phase of [[software engineering]] projects.  Key deliverables from this phase include [[Software documentation|documentation]] that describes what the system does in terms of its functional features, and how it achieves those features in terms of its [[Software architecture|architecture]] and [[Software design|design]].  [[Software architecture recovery]] is often the first step within System appreciation.<ref>{{Cite web |author1=Patel, Sandipkumar |author2=Yogesh Dandawate, John Kuriakose |url=http://softeng.polito.it/events/WESRE2006/03Dandawate.pdf |format=PDF |title=Architecture Recovery as first step in System Appreciation |publisher= }}</ref>

